# Atomic Design

Components follow Atomic Design strictly — 4 levels only. NO pages level (pages are replaced by `modules/`).

## Directory Structure

```
src/
  components/
    atoms/        → Smallest indivisible UI elements
    molecules/    → Groups of atoms functioning together
    organisms/    → Complex sections composed of molecules/atoms
    templates/    → Page-level layouts with placeholder slots
```

## Rules per Level

### Atoms
- Single UI element (button, input, label, icon)
- NO business logic, NO state management, NO service imports
- Wrap `@primer/react` components here for project-wide consistency
- Example: `atoms/Button/Button.tsx`

### Molecules
- Combine 2+ atoms into a functional group
- Minimal local state only (e.g., input focus)
- Example: `molecules/SearchField/SearchField.tsx` (Label + TextInput + IconButton)

### Organisms
- Compose molecules/atoms into distinct UI sections
- May receive data via props — NEVER import from services directly
- Example: `organisms/UserTable/UserTable.tsx`

### Templates
- Define page layout structure with slots
- NO data fetching, NO business logic
- Example: `templates/DashboardLayout/DashboardLayout.tsx`

## Components are Pure UI

- NEVER import from `services/` or `modules/`
- Receive ALL data via props — types come from service types
- Components are 100% reusable across any module

## File Structure per Component

Every component at every level follows the same file structure (see `component-structure`):

```
ComponentName/
  ComponentName.tsx
  ComponentName.module.scss
  ComponentName.types.ts     → Props use types imported from services
  ComponentName.utils.ts
  ComponentName.test.tsx
  index.ts
```
